# Day 03 â€“ VLOOKUP & HLOOKUP

## What I Learned
- **VLOOKUP** is used to retrieve data vertically from a table and is more commonly used.
- **HLOOKUP** is used to retrieve data horizontally and is less commonly used.

## Functions / Features
- `=VLOOKUP(lookup_value, table_array, col_index_num, FALSE)`
- `=HLOOKUP(lookup_value, table_array, row_index_num, FALSE)`

## Practice
- Created simple practice examples using both VLOOKUP and HLOOKUP to retrieve data from tables.

## Key Takeaways
- Always lock the table reference using **F4** to avoid reference errors when copying formulas.
- The last argument of the formula can use **FALSE** or **0**, as both mean an exact match.
